author.value: Finding aid prepared by Megan Dolan

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2016-11-08T13:00-0500</date>

unittitle.value: <emph render="italic">The Landmarks of New York</emph> Photograph Collection

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: Photographs of landmarked buildings in New York City from an exhibition curated by Barbaralee Diamonstein-Spielvogel.

p.value: Available by advance appointment only. To schedule an appointment, contact the Print Room Librarian at printroom@nyhistory.org. Photocopying undertaken by staff only. Limited to twenty exposures of stable, unbound material per day. (Researchers may not accrue unused copy amounts from previous days.)

‘The Landmarks of New York’ exhibition traveled to 82 countries under the sponsorship of the United States Department of State from 2006 to 2009 and returned home to New York for its final showing. It was exhibited at The New-York Historical Society from April 30 - July 12, 2009. The photographs in the exhibition were then donated to the New-York Historical Society by Barbaralee Diamonstein-Spielvogel, the exhibition's curator.
Individual buildings are listed in the box and folder list below. Dates listed in the finding aid were taken from the exhibition captions.
